HEADWORD: Abrenunciation
<hw>Ab`re*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>abrenuntiatio</ets>. See <er>Abrenounce</er>.]</ety> <def>Absolute
renunciation or repudiation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>abrenunciation</qex> of that truth which he so long had
professed, and still believed.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

